On May 9th, 2017 Jane bought 40 eggs. She ate one per day. Today she ran out of eggs. What is the date 24 hours later in MM/DD/YYYY?
Options:
(A) 06/19/2017
(B) 07/17/2017
(C) 06/20/2017
(D) 06/18/2017
(E) 06/15/2017
(F) 07/10/2017
output: Let's think step by step. She ate one egg per day for 40 days so she ate 40 / 1 = 4 eggs per day. She ate 4 eggs per day for 40 days so she ate 4 x 40 = 160 eggs. She ate 160 / 1 = 16 eggs per day. She ate 16 x 24 = 320 eggs in total. She ran out of eggs today so it is 320 - 160 = 240 hours later. So the answer is (C).

Infer the date from context.
